programme.title: Kirstie and Phil's Love It or List It
programme.desc: The return of the head-to-head property show in which Phil Spencer tries to persuade fed-up homeowners to sell, while Kirstie Allsopp argues for extending or redesigning. programme.title: Grand Designs: House of the Year
programme.desc: Kevin McCloud explores five more cutting-edge homes in the running for the RIBA House of the Year Award, focusing on properties that create space from the smallest of sites. They are a stylish one-bedroom living and work space with an experimental garden roof, a dark mews transformed into into a light and airy family home, a house that blends beach living and high architecture, a clever extension and a narrow beachfront garage that has been made over into an impressive home complete with art collection.(n)

programme.title: Supershoppers
programme.desc: Andi Osho and Anna Richardson present a special edition in which they investigate everything festive, offering money-saving advice on everything from food to gifts. They compare luxury toiletries and bargain-basement alternatives to find out what the difference is, with some surprising results, and look at ways to tell if a bottle of wine is good or not. Plus, how to get the best price on supermarket party platters, the truth about flash sales websites and the secrets of how high-street retailers use Santa to make sacks of cash.(n)

programme.title: Gogglebox

programme.title: It Was Alright In
programme.desc: Matt Lucas returns to narrate another light-hearted retrospective poking fun at Britain's viewing habits in the 1970s. This time, he focuses on the world of comedy, unfettered as it was to the conventions of political correctness. A selection of clips from hit TV shows illustrate how, if viewers were not straight, white, middle-class men, they were at risk of being offended, and highlights examples from On the Buses, The Two Ronnies, Dave Allen at Large and The Wheeltappers and Shunters Social Club. Includes commentary and contributions by Melvyn Hayes, Eric Chappell, Bill Oddie, Krishnan Guru-Murthy, Grace Dent, Nish Kumar, Ellie Taylor, Joel Dommett and Phil Wang.(n)

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces
programme.desc: Jan Fursier has discovered in one of her father Reg's wartime diaries an illustrated guide to building a 1930s caravan, created by her dad while held in captivity. George Clarke and Will Hardie attempt to bring the caravan to life, leading to an emotional reunion in the same Welsh national park where Reg took the family on holidays after the war.(n)

programme.title: Secret History
programme.desc: Documentary shedding light on whether there is any truth to conspiracy theorists' suggestions that London and Washington had been aware the Japanese were planning to assault the American naval base at Pearl Harbour in 1941, but refused to act on the intelligence as part of a plot to bring the full might of America's military into the Second World War. In the wake of the attack, an investigation into how US forces failed to anticipate the assault concluded that Admiral Husband Kimmel, Commander in Chief of the Pacific Fleet, had been guilty of dereliction of duty, a charge that left his career in tatters. Making use of new research into a top-secret US military project, as well as thousands of freshly unearthed documents, letters and photographs, this film aims to answer - once and for all - whether the brutal attack that claimed nearly 2,500 lives could have been prevented.(n)

Arthur is a high-school student from a dysfunctional family, and does everything in his power to avoid hanging around the house while mom and dad quarrel. Back at school, Arthur and pretty classmate Lila (Olivia Thirlby) have been bonding over their mutual love for all things geeky. programme.title: Kiss the Girls
programme.desc: Gary Fleder's thriller, based on James Patterson's novel, stars Morgan Freeman in his first outing as forensic psychologist Alex Cross. The investigation gets personal when his niece Naomi is kidnapped(n)

programme.title: Rush Hour 3
programme.desc: Brett Ratner's martial-arts action-comedy sequel starring Chris Tucker and Jackie Chan. When the Chinese Ambassador to the US is shot while divulging the whereabouts of a major Triad leader, the American authorities once again send Chief Inspector Lee and Detective James Carter into the fray. Lee quickly corners the would-be assassin, Kenji, but Lee's shock at coming face-to-face with an old friend gives the baddie just enough time to escape. Kenji's trail leads the mismatched cops to Paris, where car chases and a sequence among the under-dressed dancers of the Folies Bergère await them, plus rather a lot of dodgy French stereotypes and a finale atop the Eiffel Tower. Also starring Youki Kudoh and Noémie Lenoir, together with, in unlikely cameos, Max von Sydow and Roman Polanski(n)
he true story of Brooklyn Dodgers hitter Jackie Robinson, who in 1946 became the first African-American Major League baseball player. Chadwick Boseman, TR Knight, Harrison Ford, Nicole Beharie(n)

programme.title: American Gangster
programme.desc: Acting superstars Denzel Washington and Russell Crowe are captivating in this absorbing crime epic set in the early 1970s. Washington is real-life Harlem drug kingpin Frank Lucas, and Crowe plays Det. Richie Roberts, the N.Y. cop trying to nail him. A top-flight supporting cast is highlighted by Best Supporting Actress nominee Ruby Dee as Lucas's mother. Directed by Ridley Scott, from a script by Steven Zaillian(n)

programme.title: Dance of the Dead
programme.desc: As prom gets underway and the dead come out to play, the only hope for saving the day is the mismatched couple that can't seem to agree on anything. As the Cosa High School Senior Prom draws near, the local teens are more preoccupied with getting laid and looking good on the big night. But while local teen Jimmy (Jared Kusnitz) seems completely unfazed by all the infectious enthusiasm that's spreading through the student body, his girlfriend Lindsey (Greyson Chadwick) has thrown herself into the teenage ritual and remains determined to have the perfect romantic evening. But it's kind of difficult to enjoy an intimate dance when your classmates are trying to eat your brains, and when the tux-clad teens begin turning blue and munching on flesh, Jimmy and Lindsey are forced to put their differences aside long enough to extinguish the zombie plague before it spreads beyond campus grounds(n)

programme.desc: Comedy-adventure about a fast-talking, cigar-chomping, beer-loving duck from another dimension who somehow winds up in Cleveland and has run-ins with punk rockers, motorcycle mamas and the all-powerful overlord who make him wish he were back on his own duck planet(n)

programme.title: Peacock
programme.desc: In the tiny town of Peacock, Nebraska, quiet bank clerk John Skillpa prefers to live an invisible life. He may live by himself, but he's never alone John has two personalities. His alter ego is Emma, a well-kept secret -- until now¿ When a passing caboose jumps the rails and comes slamming through John's backyard, the neighbors all race to his aid and are surprised to find Emma. Instinctively assuming she¿s John's wife, they rally around the Skillpas in support. But the harder they try to get closer to Emma, the deeper John slips into psychosis(n)

programme.title: Eagle Eye
programme.desc: Shia LaBeouf and Michelle Monaghan star in Disturbia director D.J. Caruso's race-against-time thriller concerning two strangers thrust together by a mysterious telephone call, and their frantic efforts to discover why they have inexplicably become the nation's most wanted fugitives. Jerry Shaw (LaBeouf) and Rachel Holloman (Monaghan) were complete strangers at the beginning of the day, but that changed the instant a strange woman called to threaten both their lives and the lives of their loved ones. Suddenly forced into a series of increasingly dangerous situations, Jerry and Rachel must now take orders from a woman who's using everyday technology to track and control their every move. As the situation intensifies and the hapless duo are deemed the country's most wanted fugitives, they must work together in order to discover who it was that turned their lives upside down, and what they can do to thwart the criminal mastermind's cunning yet diabolical plan. Billy Bob Thornton, Rosario Dawson, Michael Chiklis, and Anthony Mackie co-star(n)

programme.title: Magic Mike

programme.title: Suicide Kings
programme.desc: Television director Peter O'Fallon made his feature film debut with this independent film that pays obvious homage to the style of Quentin Tarantino, with plenty of violence and funny, talkative hit men. Suave gangster Charlie Barrett (Christopher Walken) meets four young men who have taken over his regular booth at a popular bistro. Charmed by the swaggering kids, he agrees to take a ride with them, but they give him a sedative and he awakens in a deserted mansion, taped to a chair with one of his fingers missing. One of his abductors, Avery (Henry Thomas), says that he has a sister who has been kidnapped and they need two million dollars to get her back, as well as a finger to exchange for her severed digit. Charlie phones his lawyer Marty (Cliff De Young), who calls a henchman, Lono (Denis Leary), who investigates the kidnappings and gives Charlie enough information to start playing each of his inexperienced abductors against the others(n)

programme.title: When We Left Earth: The NASA Missions
programme.desc: Home in Space. The Discovery Channel's cutting-edge documentary miniseries When We Left Earth systematically (and chronologically) weaves the tale of the American Space Race, from the immediate post-WWII years into the early 20th century. Whereas episode five culminated with the Challenger disaster of January 1986, and discussed the impact it had on successive space travel, the final installment, "Home in Space," moves into the 1990s and beyond, with onscreen discussions of the Hubble telescope and its 1993 repair, the construction of the International Space Station (which commenced in 1998), the Columbia shuttle disaster of 2003, and speculations on what lies ahead in the 21st century(n)

programme.title: When We Left Earth: The NASA Missions
programme.desc: Landing the Eagle. Examining the Apollo 8, 9, 10 and 11 missions, using the huge Saturn V rocket, first orbiting and then landing on the moon. Included: interviews, archival footage. Gary Sinise narrates(n)

programme.title: When We Left Earth: The NASA Missions
programme.desc: The Explorers. The Discovery Channel's cutting-edge documentary miniseries When We Left Earth systematically (and chronologically) weaves the tale of the American Space Race, from the immediate post-WWII years into the early 20th century. The fourth episode of this series, "The Explorers," continues where the prior Apollo-themed installment left off, by visiting a crisis that nearly befell the space program in April 1970. In that now-famous series of events (later immortalized by Ron Howard's 1995 film), a series of astronauts including Fred Haise, Jim Lovell and Jack Swiegert found themselves trapped in a damaged Apollo spacecraft, faced with the slim prospect of returning the vehicle to Earth. The episode touches on their heroic success, then moves ahead into a discussion of additional moon missions during the early 1970s, and the launch and repair of Skylab, which required a never-before-done repair outside of the spacecraft in mid-orbit(n)

programme.title: When We Left Earth: The NASA Missions
programme.desc: The Shuttle. An examination of the space shuttle and its missions includes the 1986 Challenger disaster and the 2003 Columbia accident. Also: interviews and archival footage. Gary Sinise narrates(n)

programme.desc: Documentary profiling the work of Robert Rauschenberg, the influential American artist who was the first to win the Golden Lion at the Venice Biennale in 1963, and is said to have blazed a trail for creatives in the US throughout the 20th century. Rauschenberg's work has rarely been seen in the UK, but the Tate Modern is about to change that via a major new retrospective due to open this month. Ahead of the exhibition, Alastair Sooke travels to the east coast of the USA to talk to some of the people closest to Rauschenberg. His interviews provide a portrait of a man with boundless curiosity and a restlessness for experimentation, whose 60-year-long career saw him bridge the gap between the abstract expressionists of the 1950s, and the pop-art enthusiasts of the 1960s.(n)

programme.desc: The adventurer explores how the American wilderness shaped the Wild West. He begins by looking at the landscapes of three great mountain ranges - the Appalachians, the Rockies and the Sierra Nevada - and how they challenged the westward push of early pioneers. He discovers how their geography, extreme weather, wild animals and ecology provided both opportunities and challenges for those living there, and also experiences mule-trekking and gold prospecting.(n)

programme.desc: Alice Roberts visits archaeological digs in the north of Britain, where finds include evidence for the first Roman siege in the UK. There's also a look at Lindisfarne, which was violently sacked by the Vikings 1,000 years ago.(n)

programme.title: The Inca: Masters of the Clouds
programme.desc: Dr Jago Cooper presents the first of a two-part documentary reassessing the achievements of the Inca Empire. He begins his journey in the South American country of Peru, where evidence is still being uncovered that challenges theories about the empire's origins and significance. He reveals how the Inca transformed one of the world's most challenging landscapes to ward off the worst effects of the climate, and created sophisticated systems of communication. Jago also demonstrates how many independent societies were grouped together to become a commanding empire through subtle methods of persuasion as opposed to force.(n)

programme.title: A Brief History of Graffiti
programme.desc: Dr Richard Clay presents a comprehensive outline of the 30,000-year history of graffiti, from the prehistoric cave-paintings found in Burgundy, France, through to the gladiatorial fan-worship of Roman Lyon, and the messages left on the walls of the German Reichstag by Russian troops in 1945. Along the way, he unpicks the many reasons that compel people to scribble and scratch lasting mementos to their successors into any available surface, and reveals how these rudimentary memorials have developed into a legitimate art-form.(n)

programme.title: Horizon
programme.sub-title: Horizon: The Secret Life of the Dog.
programme.desc: The latest research into humans' relationship with dogs suggests that the bond between both species is controlled by a hormone also responsible for bonding mothers to their babies. The programme examines why scientists are investigating the canines more than ever before, from the latest fossil evidence to the sequencing of the genome, and how the animals might be able to perceive people's emotions as well as helping to identify genes for human diseases.(n)

programme.title: Pavlopetri - The City Beneath the Waves
programme.desc: Archaeologists use submersible robots and computer simulations to investigate the submerged city of Pavlopetri, which lies off the southern coast of the Greek mainland. Originally rediscovered in 1967, it is believed to be the oldest underwater city in the world. Philip Glenister narrates this documentary following Jon Henderson of the University of Nottingham as he leads a team of experts hoping to discover what life was like for the citizens of Pavlopetri 3,500 years ago.(n)

programme.desc: With Christmas approaching, a yearning to piece together her family history prompts a Californian woman to head to New England, where she hopes to find her father. Instead, the woman discovers the family she never knew she had. Drama, starring Erin Krakow, Wendie Malick and Niall Matter.(n)

programme.title: Mrs Miracle 2: Miracle in Manhattan
programme.desc: The kindly Mrs Merkle takes a job in the toy section of a financially struggling department store. She helps the downtrodden manager to enjoy a happy Christmas for once by making a success of the business and assisting him in his quest to find love. Family drama sequel, starring Doris Roberts, Eric Johnson, Jewel Staite and Lauren Holly.(n)

programme.title: A Perfect Christmas List
programme.desc: When she is hospitalised just before Christmas, a grandmother gives her daughter and granddaughter a list of things to do before the end of the festive season, hoping that the shared adventure will repair their strained relationship. Drama, starring Ellen Hollman, Beth Broderick and Aaron Hill.(n)

programme.title: 5 News at 5
programme.desc: Sian Williams presents a round-up of the day's headlines from around the world.(n)

programme.title: Police Interceptors
programme.desc: Kev and Steve go on the hunt for suspected heroin dealers, while dog handler Liam attends the scene of a suspected arson attack. Damo deals with a drunk driver, and another man is so inebriated behind the steering wheel that he blows three-and-a-half times over the limit.(n)

programme.title: 2016: Trump's Triumphant Year
programme.desc: It was the most controversial US Presidential campaign in living memory, but tycoon Donald Trump eventually beat Hillary Clinton to become the 45th American President-Elect. Ahead of his inauguration on January 20, 2017, this documentary looks back on Trump's road to the White House.(n)

programme.title: All New Traffic Cops
programme.desc: Traffic cops in Bradford pursue a team of suspected car thieves, travelling at speeds of 80mph. Elsewhere, North Yorkshire's Road Crime Team track down a stolen Land Rover Defender, but when a suspect makes a run for it into nearby woods, the officers are forced to give chase with nothing but a torch to help them catch their man.(n)

programme.title: The Yorkshire Vet
programme.sub-title: The Yorkshire Vet: Winter on the Moors.
programme.desc: Called out to remote farms to tend animals in labour and the sick and injured, vets Julian Norton and Peter Wright must contend with dark, cold nights, rain and snow as they battle to treat and save patients, including owls and cattle.(n)

programme.title: Ben Fogle: New Lives in the Wild
programme.desc: Dina Zughyar and Mostafa Jabbour turned their back on the American Dream to start from scratch with a handful of rabbits and chickens on a small patch of barren land in the shadow of the Atlas Mountains. In their mud house in Morocco, the Kentucky couple confess to Ben Fogle that it has been much harder than they thought. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: The Dog Rescuers with Alan Davies
programme.sub-title: The Dog Rescuers at Christmas with Alan Davies.
programme.desc: Inspector Lauren Bailey journeys to Lapland to discover how one dogsled organisation is blazing a trail for working huskies. Meanwhile, Emily Collins attempts to rescue unloved Pomeranian Freddie, left abandoned in disgusting conditions, and Pug puppy Ruby, whose jaw was broken by her owner, prepares for her first proper Christmas with Lauren.(n)

programme.title: The Secret Life of Puppies
programme.sub-title: The Secret Life of Puppies: Terrible Twos.
programme.desc: Big Ron continues to make big progress with his weight-loss programme, but now he must face his nemesis, the bath. Elsewhere, eight-month-old French Bulldog Betsy turns her hand to doggy modelling, but her pampered lifestyle has made her spoilt. Later, ten-month-old Weimaraner Atum takes part in special swimming lessons to help him get conquer his fears and learn to love the open water.(n)

programme.title: The Nightmare Neighbour Next Door
programme.sub-title: Nightmare Neighbour Next Door: When Neighbours Attack.
programme.desc: The story of Falkirk man Brian, who found himself in a six-year dispute with his neighbour over their shared-access drive. James was building a 26-room home and the number of delivery trucks began to grate on Brian - and when the two came to blows, one of them was left in hospital while the other faced trial. Plus, a marketing executive who found the more she complained about her neighbour's loud music, the more abusive the woman's boyfriend became, and a community in Bradford upset when travellers set up camp in the car park of their social club.(n)

programme.title: SuperCasino
programme.desc: Viewers get the chance to take part in live interactive gaming, with an entertaining mix of roulette-wheel spins and lively chat from the presenting team. Featuring a variety of prizes and promotions.(n)

programme.title: Under the Dome
programme.desc: The residents of Chester's Mill find themselves dealing with a new threat when the dome starts to shrink, with Rebecca warning that at its current rate it will soon crush them all. Meanwhile, Melanie's health continues to deteriorate, Barbie learns that Hunter has been secretly communicating with his father and Pauline produces another painting after encouragement from Big Jim. Sci-fi drama based on Stephen King's novel, starring Mike Vogel, Sherry Stringfield and Dean Norris.(n)

programme.title: Access
programme.desc: Showbiz news and gossip.(n)

programme.title: Person of Interest
programme.desc: Control, Hersh and their operatives hold Finch, Shaw and Claypool captive, demanding to know the location of Finch's Machine. However, the trio receive support from an unexpected quarter. Meanwhile, Reese contemplates the nature of his work. Jim Caviezel and Michael Emerson star.(n)

programme.title: Divine Designs
programme.desc: Dr Paul Binski investigates places of worship designed by Christopher Wren after the Great Fire of London in 1666. Assigned to rebuild 51 of the city's churches, he created a trademark open, auditorium-style feel to emphasise the shift from Catholic to Anglican dominance.(n)

programme.title: House Doctor
programme.desc: Ann Maurice and Alistair Appleton help a Northamptonshire woman spruce up her country cottage in the village of Welton, hoping to entice a buyer to part with £250,000. An unsightly boiler and fireplace are discreetly hidden and the lacklustre decor is brightened up to lighten the ground floor.(n)

programme.title: House Doctor
programme.desc: Property expert Ann Maurice tackles a three-bedroom terraced Victorian house in Norwich which, thanks to a vast array of deeply personal belongings, overpowering paintwork and too much furniture, has been languishing on the market for three months. A few coats of paint to neutralise the colour scheme, some effective storage ideas and a ruthless purge of useless items certainly impress the owner.(n)

programme.title: The WotWots
programme.desc: SpottyWot's chair runs out of fuel, leaving him hanging from the ship's rail.(n)

programme.title: Lily's Driftwood Bay
programme.desc: A washed-up ribbon inspires Lily to teach Salty how to fly a kite. After one-too-many disasters, Lily learns that Salty is more confident at sea and comes up with a plan to help.(n)

programme.title: Fireman Sam
programme.desc: James and Norman's pirating adventures end with them taking a quick nap and drifting out to sea.(n)

programme.title: Peppa Pig
programme.desc: Peppa and George have to tidy up their bedroom, which is soon clean with the help of Daddy and Mummy Pig - but it does not stay that way for long.(n)

programme.title: Peppa Pig
programme.desc: George and Peppa visit the playground and Daddy Pig gets a new video camera.(n)

programme.title: Bob the Builder
programme.desc: The team have to literally move a house.(n)

programme.title: Little Princess
programme.desc: The youngster decides to grow a tomato plant.(n)

programme.title: Pip Ahoy
programme.desc: A comet is due to fly over Salty Cove and everyone wants to stay awake to see it. Hopper decides to have a nap during the day so he can stay up all night - but his rest is disturbed by Alan the Penguin.(n)

programme.title: Thomas & Friends
programme.desc: Thomas takes over from Victor at the steam works, but does not pay enough attention to instructions.(n)

programme.title: Noddy: Toyland Detective
programme.sub-title: Noddy and the Case of the Amazing Eyebrows.
programme.desc: Fuse wants to wear his new eyebrows when he collects his trophy at the Toyland awards, but they have gone missing, and Noddy is accused of theft.(n)

programme.title: Ben and Holly's Little Kingdom
programme.sub-title: Journey to the Centre of the Earth.
programme.desc: Naughty Daisy and Poppy cast a spell that sends their teacher Mrs Fotheringill to the centre of the Earth, and Ben and Holly encounter dinosaurs and volcanos as Granpapa Thistle leads them on a mission to rescue her.(n)

programme.title: Wissper
programme.desc: The youngster meets Kev, a crocodile who would like to go surfing if only he could discover the knack of catching a wave.(n)

programme.title: Peppa Pig
programme.desc: George cannot catch a ball, so Mummy Pig suggests they play piggy in the middle to help him learn.(n)

programme.title: Peppa Pig
programme.desc: George and Peppa help Daddy Pig look for his glasses.(n)

programme.title: Paw Patrol
programme.desc: Cap'n Turbot's French cousin Francois tries to help get a picture of a rare blue-footed bird, but gets stuck on a cliff.(n)

programme.title: Toot the Tiny Tugboat
programme.desc: HP challenges Toot to a night-time orienteering competition, but ends up needing Toot's help when his electronic navigation system fails.(n)

programme.title: Toby's Travelling Circus
programme.desc: Li ignores the correct instructions for operating a German wheel, and Freddo does not pay attention while he and Clara are practising a new comic routine on a barrel.(n)

programme.title: The Wright Stuff
programme.desc: Matthew Wright and his guests talk about the issues of the day, with viewers calling in to offer their opinions.(n)

programme.title: 5 News Lunchtime
programme.desc: Round-up of the day's headlines from around the world.(n)

programme.title: Noel
programme.desc: The troubled lives of five New Yorkers overlap on Christmas Eve - a woman cares for her elderly mother, and a bride-to-be gets cold feet, while her fiance is followed everywhere by an obsessive waiter. Finally, a petty crook plans to injure himself so he can attend a hospital Christmas party. Drama, starring Susan Sarandon, Penelope Cruz, Alan Arkin, Paul Walker and Chazz Palminteri, who also directed, with a cameo appearance by Robin Williams. Edited for language.(n)

programme.title: Kristin's Christmas Past
programme.desc: Premiere. A woman gets the chance to go back in time and revisit her estranged family at Christmas 16 years previously, before the events that drove them apart. However, while she finds changing the past is impossible, the experience presents a perfect opportunity to learn from her mistakes and put things right in the present. Fantasy comedy, starring Shiri Appleby and Elizabeth Mitchell.(n)

programme.title: A Nanny for Christmas
programme.desc: An unemployed advertising executive gets a job as an au pair and tries to give the kids in her charge a break from their rigidly organised lives. She tries to impress an executive she is attracted to by claiming to still be in the advertising business, a deception that proves hard to maintain. Romantic comedy, starring Emmanuelle Vaugier and Richard Ruccolo.(n)

programme.title: 5 News at 5
programme.desc: Round-up of the day's headlines from around the world.(n)

programme.title: Police Interceptors
programme.desc: Justin Moffitt and Paul Faulkner chase down a gang of suspected car thieves, while it takes seven officers to stop a violent thief who tries to sink his teeth into them. Elsewhere, a drug raid turns life-threatening, and dog-handler Jimmy Grieves tries to find out what has happened to a man with a bloodied face.(n)

programme.title: 2016: Showbiz Legends We've Lost
programme.desc: A look back on a year in which several leading lights in the world of entertainment died, including David Bowie and Prince.(n)

programme.title: The Gadget Show
programme.desc: Ortis and Jon showcase the year's best Christmas buys, from student-friendly gifts to those beyond the reach of all but millionaires. Plus, Jason runs the latest toys past discerning schoolchildren and Amy shows some Dudley office workers how to party - Gadget Show-style.(n)

programme.title: GPs: Behind Closed Doors
programme.desc: Cases include recently released offender Dean, who has a history of heart problems, depression and addiction, and after three months inside, has no roof over his head. A man in his 20s is shocked to discover he has chicken pox, even though he also had it as a child, and Dr Zareena Hyder sees a young woman with Still's Disease, an unusual form of arthritis which has caused her skin to dry out, among other symptoms.(n)

programme.title: The Trafford Centre: Countdown to Christmas
programme.desc: Behind the scenes of the Manchester shopping centre as preparations for the festive season commence, with events manager Nikki Tansey spearheading operations for the first time. Ensuring the right atmosphere is everything, and Nikki heads to a Huddersfield supplier to pick up an incredible 50 miles of fairy lights, as well as enough baubles to fill a swimming pool, while also trying to book a celebrity for the switch-on ceremony.(n)

programme.title: Britain's Favourite Xmas Songs
programme.desc: A countdown of popular songs that are guaranteed to make any Christmas party go with a swing. Highlights include the Jackson 5's Santa Claus Is Coming to Town, Greg Lake's I Believe in Father Christmas, the Waitresses' Christmas Wrapping and the Pogues and Kirsty MacColl's Fairytale of New York. Is Mud's Lonely This Christmas past its sell-by date? Will Jona Lewie ever Stop the Cavalry? And where would any Christmas party be without Slade and their classic anthem Merry Xmas Everybody? But which one will top the nation's festive chart? Featuring contributions by artists, producers, video directors, composers and journalists, who shed light on the creation of the songs and their accompanying videos.(n)

programme.title: Frank Miller's Sin City
programme.desc: In this collection of crime tales set in the underbelly of a miserable metropolis, a bruiser seeks the person who killed his one-night stand. Elsewhere, a cop is framed for a series of murders, and a group of prostitutes must dispose of a dead body(n)

programme.title: Bulletproof
programme.desc: An undercover cop is given the job of tracking down a small-time crook so he can testify against a drug lord(n)

programme.title: Formula 51
programme.desc: Samuel L Jackson plays a pharmaceutical genius who has used his knowledge to make a fortune in illegal drugs, particularly with Formula 51, which is more potent than heroin, crack or anything else. But instead of selling it to his drug lord employer (Meatloaf), he jets to Liverpool where Robert Carlyle is acting as broker for Ricky Tomlinson, who's prepared to offer $20m for the formula - money Jackson would love to spend if he can stay alive long enough in Ronny Yu's fast-moving crime thriller(n)

programme.title: Be Kind Rewind
programme.desc: Jack Black and Mos Def re-enact everything from Ghostbusters to Rush Hour when the tapes in their video store are wiped. Hit slacker comedy from director Michel Gondry. (2008)(97 mins)(n)

programme.title: San Andreas
programme.desc: In this high-octane thrill ride, a helicopter pilot races to rescue his daughter and estranged wife as a series of massive earthquakes devastate California. Meanwhile, a Cal Tech professor attempts to warn other citizens(n)

programme.title: Under Siege
programme.desc: In what is widely regarded as his best film, Steven Seagal plays lowly Navy chef Casy Ryback on board the USS Missouri, a nuclear-armed battleship. But when the ship is seized by terrorist William Stranix and renegade officer Commander Krill, Ryback reveals his true identity: he's an ex-navy SEAL seeing out his time as a chef after an "incident". Now Ryback must use all his old skills to take on the baddies. Andrew Davis's all-action film co-stars Erika Eleniak as Jordan Tate, Playboy's Miss July 1989, who tags along with Ryback for safety, and acts as a foil for the humorous spats between the pair in the rare moments between the kick-ass action(n)

programme.title: Krampus
programme.desc: While Santa Claus rewards good children with gifts on Christmas, Krampus, a beast-like creature with demonic appearance, seeks out naughty children and punishes them(n)

programme.title: The Visit
programme.desc: The Visit is a comedic horror film from director M. Night Shyamalan that follows a pair of children whose lives are changed drastically when their mother (Kathryn Hahn) takes them to visit their grandparents. After seeing their grandparents engaged in activities that they had been kept as a secret to the entire family previously, they are endangered and rendered potentially unable to ever return to their previous existence. The movie co-stars Peter McRobbie and Deanna Dunagan, with music from Hans Zimmer(n)

programme.title: The Order
programme.desc: Brian Helgeland's religious thriller stars Heath Ledger as Alex Bernier, a young Catholic priest who adheres to a rare form of the faith. When he learns of the strange death of his mentor, he travels to Rome with his fellow priest Thomas Garrett and savant Mara Sinclair - a woman who once tried to kill him during an exorcism - to investigate the mystery. Brian Helgeland's religious thriller stars Heath Ledger as Alex Bernier, a young Catholic priest who adheres to a rare form of the faith. When he learns of the strange death of his mentor, he travels to Rome with his fellow priest Thomas Garrett and savant Mara Sinclair - a woman who once tried to kill him during an exorcism - to investigate the mystery. What he finds is the truth behind the myth of the Sin Eater, an immortal figure who takes on the sins of the damned to ensure their passage into Heaven. But with immortality comes both spiritual and temporal corruption, as Bernier battles both the church and demons to uncover the secrets of the Sin Eater. The film reunited the director with the stars of his film A Knight's Tale and also stars Benno Fürmann and Peter Weller(n)

programme.title: Scream 3
programme.desc: The final instalment in this hugely successful trilogy, takes place in Hollywood during production of "Stab 3, Return To Woodsboro". The production is a thriller which raises troubling questions about the events that terrified Woodsboro and continue to haunt Sidney Prescott. Three and a half years after leaving Windsor College, Sidney has settled in to a life of quiet seclusion in Northern Carolina. But that uneasy peace is shattered when terror erupts on the set of "Stab 3". Hotshot TV presenter Gale Weathers is called to the scene by the LAPD as the ultimate expert on the previous murders, and is reunited with Dewey. Will they survive to tell the tale this time?(n)

programme.title: Victor Frankenstein
programme.desc: This reimagining of the Frankenstein mythos focuses on Igor, the assistant of Victor Frankenstein. When the mad scientist builds an undead creature that soon becomes a grave danger, it's up to Igor to save Frankenstein from both the monster and himself(n)

programme.title: The Wrestler
programme.desc: Mickey Rourke stars as a has-been wrestler who heads back to the ring with hopes of a comeback in this drama helmed by director Darren Aronofsky and scripted by Robert Siegel. Marisa Tomei co-stars as Rourke's on-again, off-again paramour, the single mother of a young son with whom Rourke strikes up a rapport(n)

programme.title: Shaft
programme.desc: Dynamic Samuel L. Jackson stars as New York City cop John Shaft, who quits the force and decides to dispense his own brand of vigilante justice against a racist killer (Christian Bale) and a Dominican drug lord (Jeffrey Wright). Richard Roundtree, who played the original John Shaft in three '70s crime dramas, has a cameo as Jackson's uncle and namesake. Busta Rhymes, Vanessa Williams, Dan Hedaya(n)

programme.title: Lucky Numbers
programme.desc: John Travolta plays Russ Richards, a small-town weatherman who is such a local celebrity that he even has his own table at the local Denny's. He obviously sees himself as a big deal about town, and he's got the spending habits to prove it, including payments on a big house and a fancy Jaguar. His unstable life is further complicated by the fling he's having with the station's lotto girl, who is also having an affair with the married station manager(n)

programme.title: The Last Witch Hunter
programme.desc: An immortal witch hunter joins forces with a witch to stop a plague that could decimate the population of New York City(n)

programme.title: Cry Freedom
programme.desc: The true story of the murder of South African civil rights leader Steve Biko and the struggle to publish his story. Featuring exceptional performances from Denzel Washington and Kevin Kline(n)

programme.title: Evan Almighty
programme.desc: Emmy-nominee Steve Carell, reprising his role as the polished, preening newscaster Evan Baxter of Bruce Almighty, is the next person selected by God to perform a holy mission in this hilarious comedy. Newly elected to Congress, Evan's life is turned upside-down when God appears and mysteriously commands him to build an ark. But his befuddled family just can't decide whether Evan is having an extraordinary mid-life crisis or is truly on to something of Biblical proportions..(n)

programme.title: The Longest Ride
programme.desc: In this poignant romantic drama, a star-crossed love affair begins between a retired bull rider who wants to get back in the saddle and an art student preparing to seek her fortune in New York City. As their relationship is put to the ultimate test, the wisdom of an aging man who recalls his own lost love serves as a source of great inspiration(n)

programme.title: The Water Diviner
programme.desc: In this sweeping epic set in the Australian outback, a father gifted with the power to find water flowing underground fulfills a promise to his wife to locate their sons lost at the battle of Gallipoli(n)

programme.title: Hollywood Ending
programme.desc: A witty script and a great ensemble cast that includes Debra Messing and Tea Leoni add up to one of Woody Allen's most hilarious farces. Allen wrote, directed and stars as a washed-up filmmaker who is suddenly stricken with psychosomatic blindness on the eve of his big comeback(n)

programme.title: Vacation
programme.desc: In this hilarious installment of the "Vacation" series, the youngest son of the Griswold clan, now grown with a family of his own, sets out to re-create a cross-country road trip from his youth to an amusement park(n)

programme.title: Road House
programme.desc: Patrick Swayze leads this action movie as a bouncer who tries to bring order to a rowdy Mid West bar(n)

programme.title: Magic Mike XXL
programme.desc: Retired male stripper Magic Mike decides to help his friends put on one last show, as the crew embark on a road trip to Myrtle Beach to perform at an exotic-dance convention. Along the way, they brighten the lives of several women(n)

programme.title: Trainwreck
programme.desc: A commitment-phobic binge drinker living in New York City must reevaluate her feelings about intimate relationships when a sports doctor pursues a romance with her(n)

programme.title: The Banger Sisters
programme.desc: Comedy in which a wild woman who was a famous groupie in the 1960s makes a road trip to meet up with her former partner in crime, only to discover that her friend is now a conservative housewife and pillar of the community(n)

programme.title: The Score
programme.desc: Action packed thriller starring Robert De Niro and Edward Norton. A professional criminal decides to leave the business for good until a young thief makes him an offer he can't refuse(n)

programme.desc: David Attenborough looks at the world's caves, including the Lechuguilla Cave in America, which contains chambers filled with 6m-long crystals. programme.title: The Blue Planet
programme.desc: Predators and prey in the open oceans come under the scrutiny of David Attenborough. Marlin track down a shoal of sardines as a sei whale scoops up the leftovers, dolphins herd mackerel and attract the attention of a sailfish with the resonance of their sonar, and giant sunfish queue up to allow other species, including seagulls, to feed on their parasites.(n)

programme.title: Life in the Undergrowth
programme.desc: An exploration of how invertebrates' production of silk 300 million years ago became their greatest invention. Stronger than a steel thread of the same diameter, the material is as pliable as elastic and employed by spiders for activities as diverse as courtship, catching prey and tending their young. David Attenborough reveals how some communal spiders create silken palaces rising 15m to 20m into the forest canopy.(n)

programme.title: Great Barrier Reef
programme.desc: Monty Halls reveals how the Great Barrier Reef is vitally linked to the rest of the planet in many ways. Creatures travel thousands of miles to visit, from tiger sharks, great whales and seabirds to the largest green-turtle gathering on Earth and rarely seen alien-like creatures, such as the tentacled nautilus. The reef is also affected by weather systems travelling from across the Pacific, including cyclones that bring destruction and chaos to the coral and the creatures that live on it. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Africa
programme.desc: David Attenborough looks at the varied creatures of the Congo rainforest, one of the most competitive habitats on Earth. A sweet-toothed chimpanzee uses a complex array of tools to access honey from a beehive, the elusive picathartes bird feeds unsuspecting frogs to its dinosaur-like chicks and a massive female python reveals her maternal side as she sunbathes to incubate her eggs. Tiny leaf-folding frogs battle it out kung fu style, and as darkness falls the forest elephants gather to face their rivals.(n)

programme.desc: The Say U.N.C.L.E. Affair. As indicated by its title, this classic episode reunites the former stars of The Man From U.N.C.L.E., Robert Vaughn and David McCallum. Vaughn appears in his traditional A-Team role as the mysterious, manipulative General Stockwell, while McCallum is seen as Stockwell's former partner Ivan Trigorin, now a rogue agent who had sold out to the Other Side. Ivan kidnaps Stillwell and spirits him away to his headquarters at the Coastal Psychiatric Hospital, where he plans to exact a terrible revenge for Stillwell's supposed treachery. programme.desc: US Navy lieutenant Paul Booth is shot dead while sitting on a park bench. In the wake of the Persians' victory over King Leonidas and his 300 Spartans, the God King Xerxes (Santoro) appears poised to conquer Greece. As the ruthless Artemisia (Eva Green) assembles a massive fleet of ships and sets sail for conquest, Greek general Themistokles (Sullivan Stapleton) strives to rally his countrymen to fight for freedom, and he manages to gain the upper hand over the invaders by confronting them at sea. Meanwhile, Leonidas' former advisor and wife Queen Gorgo (Lena Headey) is reluctant to sacrifice any more Spartans in a fight that appears to be unwinnable. When the Greeks enjoy an early victory over Artemisia and her soldiers, however, it appears that Themistokles' unconventional tactics are more effective than the Persian Empire's formidable brawn. But later, after Artemisia's attempt to seduce Themistokles to her side proves unsuccessful, the spurned naval commander deals a devastating blow to her Greek opponents. In the aftermath of that skirmish, Themistokles is presumed dead and Athens falls. The Persian Empire seems on the verge of victory, though when Xerxes and Artemisia learn that Themistokles lives, they realize the fight won't be over until he takes his final breath(n)

programme.title: Last of the Summer Wine

programme.desc: A festive special of John Sullivan's sitcom from 2006. Jed, Elgin and Bryan become convinced a mythical creature is stalking Winterdown Farm, and Llewellyn accuses the Boyces' dog of seducing his pedigree collie. Nigel Harrison and Paul Bown guest star.(n)

programme.desc: Ronnie Corbett and Ronnie Barker star in a festive edition of their celebrated comedy show, first aired in 1984. programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.sub-title: Miami Twice - Part Two: Oh to Be in England.
programme.desc: Part two of two. The Trotters arrive in Florida, and walk straight into disaster after their camper van is burgled and local Mafiosi take a shine to Del-Boy, who bears more than a passing resemblance to their boss. What Del does not know is that they are planning to have him killed as a way of faking the godfather's death to help him escape being sent to prison. Feature-length episode of the comedy, starring David Jason and Nicholas Lyndhurst, with a cameo appearance by Bee Gee Barry Gibb.(n)

programme.title: Miranda
programme.desc: The first of the final two episodes of the sitcom sees the unlucky-in-love shop owner having received two proposals of marriage - one from dreamboat chef Gary and the other from new boyfriend Mike. Who will she choose, if anyone? And if she does make a decision, could she actually cope with the pressures of being a wife? Tom Ellis and Bo Poraj co-star as the rivals for her affections, with Patricia Hodge, Sarah Hadland and Sally Phillips.(n)

programme.title: Marley's Ghosts
programme.desc: In this Christmas special set against a backdrop of the local nativity play, some shocking news sets Adam and Michael against each other and it begins to seem as if things will never be quite the same for Marley and her ghosts.(n)

programme.title: Blackadder
programme.desc: It is Christmas Eve 1850, and the kindly Ebenezer Blackadder spends the festive season being taken advantage of by his relatives, his neighbours and even Queen Victoria. When he is visited by the Spirit of Christmas, he gains an insight into the dastardly deeds of his ancestors, and starts to wonder if he would be better off following in their footsteps. Comic reversal of the classic Dickens tale, starring Rowan Atkinson, Tony Robinson, Stephen Fry, Hugh Laurie, Robbie Coltrane and Miranda Richardson.(n)

programme.title: Blackadder
programme.desc: Documentary celebrating the comedy, featuring behind-the scenes footage and interviews with the actors and crew. Writers Richard Curtis and Ben Elton are among the contributors, along with cast members Stephen Fry, Hugh Laurie, Tony Robinson, Tim McInnerny, Miranda Richardson, Miriam Margolyes and Brian Blessed, producer John Lloyd and Howard Goodall, who wrote the theme tune. Narrated by David Mitchell.(n)

programme.title: Harry Hill's TV Burp
programme.desc: The quirky comic takes a characteristically surreal look at a smattering of TV programmes, subjecting soap sagas, celebrities and media stories to his unique brand of scrutiny.(n)

programme.title: The Catherine Tate Show
programme.desc: Lauren gets a tattoo of her boyfriend, only to be immediately dumped, and Nan is introduced to her grandson's girlfriend. New bride Victoria makes a memorable wedding speech in which she discloses the number of relationships she has had in the 15 years since she became sexually active.(n)

programme.title: I Dream of Jeannie
programme.desc: The genie learns of Tony's interest in the desalination of sea water, and decides to lend a hand by conjuring up the man who discovered the secret 2,000 years earlier - her great-grandfather. Vintage comedy about a lovelorn genie, starring Barbara Eden and Larry Hagman.(n)

programme.title: I Dream of Jeannie
programme.desc: Major Jamison is concerned about his son when the lad claims he saw Tony floating in mid-air - on a beach towel. Vintage comedy about a lovelorn genie, starring Barbara Eden and Larry Hagman.(n)

She reads his palm and tells him that he needs a woman; she then hands him Love Potion No. 8 which will attract women like flies to honey. Though the changes only last four hours per dose, they are truly remarkable and the two agree to separate for three weeks and then come back together to compare results. The time passes quickly and wonderfully for them and when they finally reunite both have changed for the better. Just for fun, they decide to go out with each other. They do not drink the potion, but still have a wonderful and passionate night. This leads Paul to propose to Diane. Unfortunately, she thinks she loves another, a man who is really more interested in exploiting the potion for money than he is in her. He ends up buying up all of Madame Ruth's latest batch. Paul goes back to her and explains his problem and that is when Ruth hands him the potent Love Potion No. 9, which can manifest true love. programme.title: Smokin' Aces
programme.desc: When a shifty magician turns state's evidence against a Las Vegas underworld heavy, the high price placed on his head sparks a fevered race to rub the snitch out and collect a tidy paycheck in Narc director Joe Carnahan's dark action comedy. Buddy "Aces" Israel (Jeremy Piven) is a small-time scammer who has somehow managed to get the goods on big-time mobster Primo Sparazza. Upon discovering that Buddy is about to deliver the evidence needed to get him thrown in jail for life, Primo takes out a sizable contract on Buddy that entices every two-bit thug, grizzled bounty hunter, deadly vixen, skilled assassin, and ladder-climbing Mafioso within a hundred-mile radius into taking a shot at the prize. Now holed up in his luxurious Lake Tahoe hideout with only two FBI agents (Ryan Reynolds and Ray Liotta) standing between him from a virtual army of money-hungry rogues, Buddy is about to find out just how far this motley crew of killers is willing to go in order to take him out and hit the jackpot. Ben Affleck, Jason Bateman, Andy Garcia, Alicia Keys, and Martin Henderson co-star in a bullet-strewn, ensemble crime comedy that never stops to reload(n)

programme.title: Knockaround Guys
programme.desc: A big score goes wrong in a big way for a bunch of aspiring gangsters in this crime comedy. Matty Demaret (Barry Pepper) is the son of a mid-level Brooklyn mob boss, Benny "Chains" Demaret (Dennis Hopper). When Matty was 12 years old, Benny and Uncle Teddy (John Malkovich) decided to see if Matty had what it took to be in the mob; they gave the boy a gun and ordered him to shoot a longtime enemy of the family. Matty lacked the nerve to do it, and ever since, Benny has been convinced his son is a coward. As an adult, Matty is stuck between a rock and a hard place; he'd like to work as a sports agent, but his family's criminal ties make that all but impossible, and his dad won't give him a chance in the family's operations. Uncle Teddy decides to give Matty a chance to make good by asking him to pick up a payment of $500,000 in Spokane, WA. Matty puts together a crew of three friends, all sons of mob guys, to help him out: muscle bound Taylor (Vin Diesel), ladies' man Chris (Andrew Davoli), and cocaine-addled would-be pilot Johnny (Seth Green). Getting the money goes just fine, but during a refueling stop in Montana, Johnny has to hide the money to keep it from being discovered. It's then promptly stolen by a pair of burnouts. When Matty and his crew discover the money is missing, they head back to Montana, but before long, they find out that the sheriff (Tom Noonan) is onto them, and that he has his own plans for the cash; they also learn that Uncle Teddy has some plans he didn't tell them about. programme.sub-title: Whitestaunton, Somerset: A Roman Bath and Edwardian Folly.
programme.desc: Tony Robinson visits a medieval manor house in Somerset to investigate the remains of a possible Roman villa that was first uncovered in a boggy area at the bottom of a garden in 1883. After draining the swamp, the team soon finds walls, floors and mosaics.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Health-conscious grandmother Tina Ainsworth hosts the first dinner party in Mansfield, Nottinghamshire, putting on a Chinese-themed evening for her guests - croupier Tomasz Wisniewski, PR consultant Julia Smith, copy writer Rachel Imms and DJ Gareth Harding.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Croupier Tomasz Wisniewski hosts the second dinner party in Mansfield, Nottinghamshire. His `outrageous'-themed evening leaves plenty of scope for his guests' imaginations, but his balloon-pumping competition brings out the competitive streak in one contestant.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: DJ Gareth Harding hosts the third dinner party from Mansfield, Nottinghamshire, where he provides an Ibiza-themed night after he transforms his garden into a Balearic cocktail bar and club complete with lasers and disco lights. The guests seem impressed with the host's sophisticated menu, but he may have bitten off more than he can chew as he attempts to cook a tricky beef Wellington.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Animal lover Rachel Imms hosts the fourth party of the week from Mansfield. She opts for a French-themed evening, but her complicated main course proves to be a challenge, and her accordionist entertainer does not appeal to everyone in the way she had hoped.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Dance fanatic Julia Smith hosts the final party in Mansfield, Nottinghamshire, and is confident she will wow fellow competitors with her fancy house and hospitality, having roped in two waiters to give the evening a touch of class. A spot of salsa dancing proves entertaining for all the wrong reasons, and as the event draws to a close, the contestants gather to discover which dinner was rated the best.(n)

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces
programme.desc: The architect finishes work on his project to transform his unloved back garden into a creative family space, and heads to Cambridgeshire, where he meets a DIY perfectionist who is hoping to build the smallest-ever campervan. In Somerset, George finds out about a local man's plan to turn a horse trailer into a mobile cheese stall and food festival attraction.(n)

programme.title: Car SOS
programme.desc: Tim Shaw and mechanic Fuzz Townshend go to Leeds to repair British sports car the AC Aceca, which has been kept and loved by its owner Monet since the early 1970s.(n)

programme.title: The Supervet
programme.desc: Following the work of `Bionic Vet' Noel Fitzpatrick and his team at a pioneering veterinary practice. Maya, a Russian Blue cat, is brought into the surgery with a shattered jaw after a dog attack, and a man living in a homeless shelter brings in his best friend Spud, a Labrador cross with a lame back leg. Plus, Noel tries to help straighten a deformity in a six-month-old Chihuahua puppy's leg.(n)

programme.title: Grand Designs
programme.desc: Simon and Jasmine Dale take on the challenging task of building a 21st-century, low-impact three-bedroom family home with a budget of only £500. As part of a pioneering, government-backed, sustainable village called Lammas, the couple must adhere to their fierce planning conditions of self-sufficiency or risk losing everything.(n)

programme.title: Car SOS
programme.desc: Presenter Tim Shaw and master mechanic Fuzz Townshend head to Cambridge to rescue a cherished 1991 Range Rover Vogue SE, which is in need of some TLC.(n)

programme.title: 8 Out of 10 Cats
programme.desc: Irreverent panel show, hosted by Jimmy Carr. Team captains Rob Beckett and Aisling Bea are joined by guest panellists Chris Kamara, Tom Davis, James Acaster and Tiff Stevenson to answer questions based on opinion polls carried out around the country to see who best understands what is going on in Britain today.(n)

programme.title: 999: What's Your Emergency
programme.desc: The challenges faced by emergency services on the roads, revealing how new technology can detect people driving under the influence of drugs, leading to a rise in convictions. A woman is found to be over the limit while driving only a few streets away from her home. Emergency services personnel reveal the problems they have when dealing with elderly motorists who may no longer be able to drive safely, and how responding to an incident can have lasting repercussions.(n)

programme.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
programme.desc: Gordon Ramsay gives his advice to Paul Bazzini, an award-winning chef from New York who now owns a restaurant in Ridgewood, New Jersey. Paul confesses he has lost his passion for food and is struggling to keep up with the business, a situation that seems evident to other members of staff, his wife and customers.(n)

programme.title: Car SOS
programme.desc: Presenter Tim Shaw and master mechanic Fuzz Townshend head to Cambridge to rescue a cherished 1991 Range Rover Vogue SE, which is in need of some TLC.(n)

programme.title: 8 Out of 10 Cats Does Countdown
programme.desc: Jimmy Carr hosts the comedy panel show's version of the famous quiz, with team captains Sean Lock and Jon Richardson joined by guests Rhod Gilbert and Sara Pascoe. Countdown regular Susie Dent is assisted in Dictionary Corner by Johnny Vegas, while Rachel Riley provides the letters and numbers with a little help from Joey Essex.(n)

programme.title: 8 Out of 10 Cats
programme.desc: Team captains Sean Lock and Jon Richardson are joined by celebrity guests Steve Jones, David O'Doherty, Deborah Meaden and Seann Walsh to discuss and dissect the events that set the British public's chins wagging over the past week. Jimmy Carr hosts the topical comedy panel show.(n)

programme.title: Kirstie's Handmade Treasures
programme.desc: Kirstie Allsopp joins members of a Women's Institute group and together they learn needle felting and how to make a mosaic. However, teaming up is a first for the presenter and they all try to agree on their final entry for the New Forest and Hampshire County Show.(n)

programme.title: Food Unwrapped
programme.desc: Kate Quilton travels to Thailand to find out how seafood sticks are made, while Martin Dickie is on board a French floating factory ship, discovering the role an ancient Japanese fish-processing technique plays in manufacturing the products. Kate also investigates the difference between English and British wine, learning that many examples of the latter are not created using homegrown grapes.(n)

programme.title: Grand Designs
programme.desc: Kevin McCloud meets Katrin and James Gray, who have bought a disused solarium on the roof of flats in Bournemouth, to convert into a luxury penthouse with stunning views of England's south coast. However, they do not realise the problems that building on top of another structure can bring, and find themselves having to move heavy materials six storeys high, with 60 angry neighbours to placate.(n)

programme.title: The Spy Who Came in from the Cold
programme.desc: A burnt-out British spy is ordered to venture undercover in East Germany. He begins by faking his resignation and subsequent alcoholic depression to dupe the enemy into trusting him, but, as he becomes further embroiled in his mission, he comes to realise that he is merely a pawn. Espionage thriller, based on John Le Carre's novel, starring Richard Burton, Claire Bloom, Oskar Werner and Peter Van Eyck.(n)

programme.title: Time Team
programme.desc: Tony Robinson and the team of experts set out to uncover the facts behind a collection of human bones - some of which appear to be children's - found in a Derbyshire cave. A possibly prehistoric burial mound located near the site could hold the answers.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Hunting enthusiast Hunni Hindley hosts the first party in Lincoln, basing it on a murder-mystery theme and concocting an unconventional menu in the hope of landing the £1,000 prize. There is a heated debate on hunting, and the other guests provide interesting discourse including Ricky Summers-Calvert, who has a revelation to make about his acting career.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Medical supplier Caroline Bevis hosts the second dinner party in Lincoln, hoping her Roaring Twenties-themed evening, including black-bottom Betty torte with beetroot ice-cream, will secure her the £1,000 prize.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Insurance underwriter Glenn Priestly hosts the third dinner party from Lincoln, and hopes his theme of rock music legends will win over his guests. However, the tone of the evening is lowered by student Richard Summers-Calvert's inappropriate questions.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Bodybuilding drama student Richard Summers-Calvert hosts the fourth party of the week from Lincoln. He serves chicken and rice for his starter, main and dessert, but with a few twists, and entertains his guests with a game of charades after asking them to dress up as action heroes.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: All-American mother and former barrister Natashka Ingham hosts the final dinner party from Lincolnshire, and hopes to impress her guests with a theme of The Great American Dream. Her dishes include `fall off your horse black bottom pie' and `cow tail pie' and, despite the fact conversation turns to underpants and toilets, she hopes to have done enough to win the £1,000 cash prize.(n)

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces
programme.desc: The architect heads off to Italy, where it seems the residents have also been bitten by the `small buildings are beautiful' bug. The most spectacular place he visits is so high up in the mountains that it's only accessible by helicopter, but this difficulty is more than made up for by the views seen from it. Back in Britain, George meets a man turning a wrecked private jet into a crash pad and a Gypsy tattoo artist with big plans for an old railway carriage. George also challenges his pal, craftsman Will Hardie, to create a woodland retreat for less than the price of a family holiday.(n)

programme.title: Car SOS
programme.desc: Tim Shaw and mechanic Fuzz Townshend head to West Sussex to rescue an iconic 1970s motor - and the first truly successful Japanese car export - the mighty Datsun 240z.(n)

programme.title: The Supervet
programme.desc: Senior neurologist Dr Colin Driver comes up with an unconventional solution to treat a nurse's cat, which has been rushed into the surgery after being poisoned. Meanwhile, the owners of a rare Polish sheepdog with a failed fracture repair on a broken leg are faced with the option of having the leg removed, or trying an innovative total elbow replacement. Plus, a self-confessed `crazy cat lady' brings in a ginger tom which urgently needs leg surgery.(n)

programme.title: Father Ted
programme.desc: The first episode of the hit comedy. The Craggy Island cleric dreams of achieving stardom on the Faith of Our Fathers TV show - but his hopes are dashed by Jack and Dougal's untimely intervention. Dermot Morgan, Ardal O'Hanlon and Frank Kelly star.(n)

programme.title: Father Ted
programme.desc: A sense of dread descends on Craggy Island as the priests prepare for poker-faced Father Stone's annual visit - and Ted tries desperately to think of a scheme to get rid of him. Clerical comedy, starring Dermot Morgan.(n)

programme.title: Ireland with Ardal O'Hanlon
programme.desc: New series. Comic actor Ardal O'Hanlon explores the Emerald Isle and Irish life, as he heads off the beaten track to learn more about his beloved homeland. In the first episode, Ardal examines Irish stereotypes and issues surrounding belief, looking at the history of many well known tales featuring leprechauns, fairies and ghost hunting, and questions why the people of Ireland are so predisposed to faith.(n)

programme.title: Small, Far Away: The World of Father Ted
programme.desc: Documentary first shown in 2011 following Graham Linehan and Arthur Mathews, who created Father Ted, as they embark on a road trip across Ireland in celebration of the 15th anniversary of the comedy's birth. They revisit some of the key locations from the series, and reflect on how producer Geoffrey Perkins suggested turning a one-off spoof documentary into a sitcom. With contributions by Ardal O'Hanlon, Frank Kelly, Graham Norton and more.(n)

programme.title: Father Ted
programme.desc: Mrs Doyle wins a competition to meet a famous singer, and discreetly invites him round for tea - but the secret slips out, and soon the house is besieged by hordes of adoring pensioners. Comedy, starring Dermot Morgan, Ardal O'Hanlon and Pauline McLynn.(n)

programme.title: Father Ted

programme.title: The Curse of the Pink Panther
programme.desc: Inspector Clouseau vanishes without trace and another detective must be chosen to solve the mystery of his disappearance. Glad to be rid of the bane of his existence, Clouseau's long-suffering boss makes sure an even more inept investigator gets the job. Comedy, starring Herbert Lom, Ted Wass, Joanna Lumley, David Niven and Robert Wagner.(n)

programme.title: Never Been Kissed
programme.desc: A clumsy 25-year-old would-be reporter is given the chance to prove herself when she is sent on an assignment to get an inside take on high-school life. However, when she falls for an English teacher, she has trouble maintaining the facade of a calm and sophisticated young lady, as all the bad memories of her awkward younger days come flooding back. Romantic comedy, with Drew Barrymore, Michael Vartan and David Arquette.(n)

programme.title: Hot Shots
programme.desc: A pilot joins an elite squad to take part in a dangerous mission, but faces a struggle to live down his father's bad reputation - and win the love of a glamorous psychiatrist. Comedy spoofing action movies - principally Top Gun - starring Charlie Sheen, Lloyd Bridges, Valeria Golino, Cary Elwes, Kevin Dunn and William O'Leary.(n)

programme.title: Hot Shots! Part Deux
programme.desc: A misunderstood soldier who has retired to a Buddhist monastery is drawn back into action for a special mission. A succession of failed rescue attempts has left countless American servicemen held hostage in the Middle East, and it falls to him to set them free. Spoof action movie sequel, starring Charlie Sheen, Valeria Golino, Lloyd Bridges and Rowan Atkinson.(n)

programme.title: Spy - Extended Version
programme.desc: A deskbound CIA agent provides valuable background support for a dashing secret agent, but has never gone into action herself. Everything changes, when the spy mysteriously vanishes, and she leaps into action to take his place, infiltrating the inner circle of a ruthless arms dealer and trying to avert a global catastrophe. Comedy adventure, starring Melissa McCarthy, Jason Statham and Rose Byrne.(n)

programme.title: Vacation
programme.desc: Family man Rusty Griswold spent his childhood family holidays stumbling from one disaster to another with his hapless father. He is determined that his own road trip with his wife and kids will go better - but soon finds the apple has not fallen far from the tree. Sequel to the 1980s comedy series, starring Ed Helms and Christina Applegate, with Chevy Chase and Beverly D'Angelo reprising their roles.(n)

programme.title: 50 First Dates
programme.desc: A vet working at a Hawaiian zoo falls madly in love with a beautiful woman and pulls out all the stops to romance her. However, his attempts to woo her are seriously undermined by the fact that she suffers from short-term memory-loss, meaning he has to resume his courtship from scratch every day. Romantic comedy, starring Drew Barrymore, Adam Sandler, Rob Schneider and Dan Aykroyd.(n)

programme.title: Jerry Maguire
programme.desc: An idealistic sports agent produces a mission statement at work promising to treat clients fairly. Unfortunately, it costs him his job. Forced to set up an agency on his own, the only people prepared to stand by him are a lovelorn staff accountant and a footballer. Cameron Crowe's romantic comedy drama, with Tom Cruise, Renee Zellweger, Kelly Preston, Jonathan Lipnicki, and Cuba Gooding Jr, who won an Oscar for his performance.(n)

programme.title: Spy - Extended Version
programme.desc: A deskbound CIA agent provides valuable background support for a dashing secret agent, but has never gone into action herself. Everything changes, when the spy mysteriously vanishes, and she leaps into action to take his place, infiltrating the inner circle of a ruthless arms dealer and trying to avert a global catastrophe. Comedy adventure, starring Melissa McCarthy, Jason Statham and Rose Byrne.(n)

programme.desc: Family man Rusty Griswold spent his childhood family holidays stumbling from one disaster to another with his hapless father. Sequel to the 1980s comedy series, starring Ed Helms and Christina Applegate, with Chevy Chase and Beverly D'Angelo reprising their roles.(n)

programme.title: Team America: World Police
programme.desc: An American counter-terrorism unit travels around the world on the lookout for threats to global peace, causing much destruction to major world cities in the process. The biggest current menace is North Korean leader Kim Jong-il and an organisation much closer to home - the Film Actors Guild. Satirical puppet comedy, voiced by South Park creators Trey Parker and Matt Stone.(n)

programme.title: Bad Santa
programme.desc: A grumpy alcoholic safe-cracker takes a job as an in-store Father Christmas with a view to robbing his employers' premises - but a bullied child, a barmaid with a Santa fetish and an overzealous security guard look set to wreck his plans for an inside job. Black comedy, starring Billy Bob Thornton, Tony Cox, Brett Kelly, Lauren Graham, Bernie Mac and John Ritter.(n)

programme.title: Lake Placid
programme.desc: A palaeontologist, a game warden, a conspiracy theorist and a redneck sheriff each set out to investigate a mysterious death on the shore of a lake, only to find themselves up against a man-eating 30ft crocodile with an insatiable appetite. Comedy horror, starring Bill Pullman, Bridget Fonda, Oliver Platt, Brendan Gleeson and Betty White.(n)

programme.title: Son of the Pink Panther
programme.desc: Comedy sequel which sees Inspector Clouseau's over-enthusiastic son on the trail of a kidnapped princess, proving to be just as inept as his father every step of the way. Starring Roberto Benigni, Herbert Lom, Claudia Cardinale, Burt Kwouk, Debrah Farentino and Graham Stark.(n)

programme.title: Nine Months
programme.desc: A child psychologist's well-ordered world begins to fall apart when his live-in girlfriend announces she is pregnant. Not fond of children anyway, he dreads the impact a baby will make on his life - and to make matters worse, their eccentric Russian obstetrician admits he has never delivered a baby before. Romantic comedy, starring Hugh Grant, Julianne Moore, Jeff Goldblum, Joan Cusack and Tom Arnold, with Robin Williams in a cameo role.(n)

programme.title: In Her Shoes
programme.desc: Two sisters have little in common - one is a financially irresponsible flirt and the other is a mature and staid lawyer. However, the pair are brought together when a dark family secret comes to light. Curtis Hanson's comedy drama, based on a novel by Jennifer Weiner, starring Cameron Diaz, Toni Collette and Shirley MacLaine.(n)

programme.title: The Holiday
programme.desc: Two single women living on opposite sides of the Atlantic agree to exchange houses over the Christmas holidays. In their new surroundings, both women unexpectedly encounter prospective partners, but as the house swap draws to a close, difficult decisions have to be made about their blossoming relationships. Romantic comedy, starring Cameron Diaz, Kate Winslet, Jack Black, Jude Law and Eli Wallach.(n)

programme.title: Hot Pursuit
programme.desc: An uptight, accident prone police officer desperate to prove herself has to protect a gangster's widow who has agreed to give evidence against a drug lord. They end up forced to go on the run together, and are pursued across Texas by hitmen and corrupt cops. Crime comedy, starring Reese Witherspoon and Sofia Vergara.(n)

programme.title: Ted 2: Extended Edition
programme.desc: The foul-mouthed talking teddy bear is horrified to discover that he counts as property according to the law. He and his human best friend hire a pot-smoking lawyer to help them fight a court case and get Ted legally recognised as a person. Comedy sequel, starring Mark Wahlberg and Amanda Seyfried, with the voice of Seth MacFarlane.(n)

programme.title: Notting Hill
programme.desc: A recently divorced bookshop owner finds love with a glamorous Hollywood film star, but ends up the focus of unwanted media interest - which makes maintaining a relationship a tricky proposition. Romantic comedy written by Richard Curtis, starring Hugh Grant, Julia Roberts, Rhys Ifans, Emma Chambers, James Dreyfus and Gina McKee.(n)

programme.title: Loser
programme.desc: A hard-working college student is branded a loser by his roommates, who promptly oust him from their group. When he helps a girl deal with an unpleasant drugs-related experience, he falls madly in love with her - but she only has eyes for a professor. Comedy, starring Jason Biggs, Mena Suvari, Greg Kinnear, Zak Orth, Thomas Sadoski and Dan Aykroyd.(n)

programme.title: Grimsby
programme.desc: Two brothers are separated at birth, the younger growing up to be MI6's top agent while the older becomes a layabout football hooligan. When they are finally reunited, the dim-witted elder sibling ends up helping his brother foil an evil plan that threatens the entire world. Action comedy, starring Sacha Baron Cohen, Mark Strong and Rebel Wilson.(n)

programme.title: Ted 2: Extended Edition
programme.desc: The foul-mouthed talking teddy bear is horrified to discover that he counts as property according to the law. He and his human best friend hire a pot-smoking lawyer to help them fight a court case and get Ted legally recognised as a person. Comedy sequel, starring Mark Wahlberg and Amanda Seyfried, with the voice of Seth MacFarlane.(n)

programme.title: DuckTales the Movie: Treasure of the Lost Lamp
programme.desc: Scrooge McDuck and great-nephews Huey, Dewey and Louie lead an archaeological expedition to find a long-lost genie's lamp once belonging to a notorious bandit, but reckon without a villainous attempt to use its powers in a dastardly plot. Animated Disney adventure, with the voices of Christopher Lloyd, Alan Young and Russi Taylor.(n)

programme.title: Beauty and the Beast
programme.desc: A bookish woman agrees to take her father's place as prisoner of a fearsome monster living in a castle deep in the forest. She gradually grows to see a gentler, more human side to her hideous host, and comes to realise she may be able to break the curse that turned him into a beast in the first place. Disney animated fantasy, with the voices of Paige O'Hara and Robby Benson.(n)

programme.title: Aladdin
programme.desc: A street urchin is caught up in a scheming grand vizier's plot to get his clutches on a magical lamp. Retrieving the object from a wondrous cave, he releases a powerful genie trapped inside, whose ability to grant wishes helps the young hero thwart the villain's plans and woo a princess. Animated adventure, featuring the voices of Robin Williams, Scott Weinger and Linda Larkin.(n)

programme.title: Tangled
programme.desc: A baby princess's hair has mystical powers, so an evil witch kidnaps her and locks her in a tower, hoping to use the magic to fend off old age. When the princess is a teenager with 70-foot long tresses, she escapes with the aid of a bandit and goes in search of her home, but the witch is not going to let her go without a fight. Disney animated comedy based on the Rapunzel story, with the voices of Mandy Moore and Zachary Levi.(n)

programme.title: Cinderella
programme.desc: An orphaned girl is treated as a servant by her cruel stepmother and her two daughters. Her life is changed for ever by the intervention of a kindly fairy godmother, who gives her the opportunity to attend a lavish royal and win the heart of a handsome prince. Romantic fantasy, starring Lily James, Cate Blanchett, Richard Madden and Helena Bonham Carter.(n)

programme.title: The Santa Clause 2
programme.desc: After eight years as Father Christmas, divorced dad Scott Calvin has settled nicely into the role. He is looking forward to another season when he discovers that a clause in his contract means he has to find a wife by Christmas Eve. Disney comedy adventure sequel, with Tim Allen, Elizabeth Mitchell, Judge Reinhold, Spencer Breslin and Eric Lloyd.(n)

programme.desc: Festive Disney short in which Mickey and Pluto pick out a tree for Christmas and bring it back home, completely unaware that cheeky chipmunks Chip and Dale are already living in it.(n)

Disney adaptation of Mark Twain's classic tale, starring Elijah Wood, Courtney B Vance, Robbie Coltrane, Jason Robards, Dana Ivey, Anne Heche and Ron Perlman.(n)

Children's fantasy, starring Walter Brennan, Matthew Garber and Karen Dotrice.(n)

Crime thriller, starring Abigail Breslin, Sean Bean and Alexa Vega.(n)

Starring Jake Gyllenhaal, Robert Downey Jr, Mark Ruffalo and Brian Cox.(n)

Action thriller sequel, starring Clint Eastwood, Patricia Clarkson, Liam Neeson and an early appearance by Jim Carrey.(n)

Drama, starring Katie Holmes, William Fichtner and JE Freeman.(n)

Thriller, starring Michael Douglas, Glenn Close and Anne Archer.(n)

Festive comedy, starring Jim Broadbent, Rafe Spall and Warwick Davis.(n)

programme.title: The Night Before

Comedy, starring Joseph Gordon-Levitt, Seth Rogen and Anthony Mackie.(n)

Comedy horror, starring Toni Collette and Emjay Anthony.(n)

programme.desc: Istvan Szabo's FilmFour-funded epic film traces the 20th century history of a Hungarian Jewish family through three generations, from peasantry to early respectability under the Hapsburgs; cruelties and death under the Nazis and, in the post-war communist years, a political enthusiasm for the new order only to realise it too is totalitarian. He'll make a killing on the bets placed on the players while the contestants dash for the cash(n)
